Dear tUME version 00.2667 user:				June 18, 2000

There are five zip files on this disk:

TUME2667.ZIP	tUME version 00.2667. Unzip into directory \TUME
DUMPTUME.ZIP	source code for DumptUME. Unzip -d into directory \DUMPTUME
TPMCKID2.ZIP	source code for TPMCKID2. Unzip -d into directory \DUMPTUME
TUMETOOL.ZIP	executables for tUME support tools. Unzip into directory \TUME
EXAMPLES.ZIP	example LBMs and MAPs for tUME. Unzip into \TUME\EXAMPLES

You should add \TUME to your PATH environment variable.

To run tUME, type TUME at the DOS prompt.

To view the demo, change to the \TUME\EXAMPLES directory, and type DEMOTUME.
Your PATH must include \TUME for the demo to operate properly.

Dan
